On January 22, 2013, the White House Office of the Press Secretary announced several nominations sent to the Senate. The nominations included John Owen Brennan to be the Director of the Central Intelligence Agency, Charles Timothy Hagel to be the Secretary of Defense, John Forbes Kerry to be the Secretary of State, Jacob J. Lew to be the Secretary of the Treasury, and Sylvia M. Becker to be a Member of the Foreign Claims Settlement Commission of the United States. Other nominations included Robert F. Cohen, Jr. to be a Member of the Federal Mine Safety and Health Review Commission, Richard J. Engler to be a Member of the Chemical Safety and Hazard Investigation Board, and David Medine to be Chairman and Member of the Privacy and Civil Liberties Oversight Board. The list also included nominations for various other positions in government agencies such as the Department of Health and Human Services, the Broadcasting Board of Governors, and the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission.